Managed by the Broward Center for the Performing Arts Please visit the Broward Center's Box Office Page for more information regarding ticketing matters. You can also email them at boxoffice@browardcenter.org or by calling 954.462.0222. For in person ticket sales and information at the Rose and Alfred Miniaci Performing Arts location, we are only open 1 hours prior to the ticketed event date/time.     • Broward for the Performing Arts Frequently Asked Questions Where is the best place to park? Parking is available in the Alvin Sherman Library parking garage. Patrons visiting the Rose and Alfred Miniaci Performing Arts Center must enter the parking garage from one of the two east entrances. Public parking cost is $1.00 per hour. Parking fees can be paid by using the PayByPhone App or at the pay booth in advance.  There are two pay booths located near the elevators in the southeast corner of the garage. You will need your car tag number to make a payment. First Floor Location Code:  15804 All Others Code:  15803 For help with parking issues please contact NSU Public Safety at 954-262-8999. When should I arrive for the event or performance? Our lobby and box office opens one hour prior to your scheduled event, we recommed arriving 45 minutes prior to your event. What food and beverages are available at events? For ticketed performances, our concession stand offers beer, wine, soda, water and a variety of light snacks. There are a handful of unique dinning experiences that you can enjoy while visiting NSU and the Rose and Alfred Miniaci Performing Arts Center. Please visit NSU Shark Dining for a map of those locations on campus. For information about hosting a catered event please contact NSU's Shark Dining Catering More Questions > Home Tickets Visit Host An Event About Summer Camp Support Accessibility Press Contact Privacy

Lauderdale, Florida. The performing arts center supports many NSU academic engagements as well as promoting and contributing to the cultural life of the NSU community and of the community at large. The Broward Center for the Performing Arts, as managing partner of the theater, provides additional cultural programming opportunities for Broward County residents, University students and faculty members. Many quality productions have already taken place at the Rose and Alfred Miniaci Performing Arts Center, and through the Center’s rental program, yours can be one of them. Let us give you the warm friendly welcome we enjoy extending to each of our guests. The Rose and Alfred Miniaci Performing Arts Center hosts a diverse mix of intimate concerts, lectures, plays and performances that include community and family fare. For more information about renting the Rose and Alfred Miniaci Performing Arts Center, e-mail MiniaciPAC@nova.edu or call 954.262.5480 . Technical Rider Rose and Alfred Miniaci Performing Arts Technical Spec FY24 v08.pdf Rental Rates MiniaciPAC - Rental Rates and Fee Schedule - FY25.pdf Alternative Facility Rentals If you are looking to book any of the other facilities on the Nova Southeastern Camp or for an outdoor catered event pre or post show, the NSU courtyard is the perfect spot just outside our doors. Please contact Nova Southeastern Facilities Management for more information on the courtyard or other event spaces you may be internested in. Rick Case Arena at the Don Taft University Center The Rick Case Arena at the Don Taft University Center is home court to NSU's NCAA Sharks basketball and volleyball teams, but it is also available for rental. The venue holds many community events throughout the year, including local high school graduations, concerts, comedians, cheerleading competitions, Special Olympics, banquets, guest speakers, business meetings and other sporting events. Insurance for Facility Usage If you do have insurance, you will need to add "Nova Southeastern University" and “Performing Arts Center Authority” as additional insureds. Any group that does not have insurance and desires to hold an event at the Rose and Alfred Miniaci Performing Arts Center on the Nova Southeastern University property please click here for instructions and details on how to obtain a certificate. You will also need to apply the additionally insured as stated above and per the contract. Please review your contract with the details outlined. Students achieve academic excellence and professional distinction as artists, leaders, and communicators, and they share their talents with the community through production, performance, and research. Shanti Bruce, Ph.D.,  Chair / Professor Department of  Communication, Media, and the Arts NSU Halmos College of Arts and Sciences The Department of Communication, Media, and the Arts (DCMA) is an innovative, learner-centered department that delivers experiential, industry-driven programs. Students achieve academic excellence and professional distinction as artists, leaders, and communicators, and they share their talents with the community through production, performance, and research. DCMA serves as a cultural resource for the university and the community, providing opportunities for artistic expression and appreciation. We invite you to visit our wonderful facilities, meet with our outstanding faculty, and witness our students’ creativity to see how DCMA can help you cultivate your creative self.
